description: Prefer short, clear function and variable names; avoid redundant prefixes
alwaysApply: true
---

# Concise naming

Use **short names that read clearly in context**. Prefer one precise word over a stacked phrase.

## Functions

- Name for **what it returns or does**, not every input type: `hasRepoHeadings(workSection)` not `completedWorkHasPerRepoHeadings(completedWorkSection)`.
- Drop redundant scope when the file/module already provides it (`enforce-standup-draft-structure.ts` → `structureWorkByRepo`, not `structureCompletedWorkByRepoForMultiRepo`).
- Boolean checks: `hasX`, `isX`, `canX` — not `xHasYAndZ`.
- Avoid `regroup`, `enforce`, `apply` chains in the same name unless each word adds meaning.

## Variables

- Parameters: `workSection`, `summarySection`, `repoGroups` — not `completedWorkSectionBodyMarkdown`.
- Locals: `bullets`, `byRepo`, `parsed` — not `whatIDidBulletLinesArray`.

## When longer names are OK

- Public API crossing package boundaries where ambiguity is real.
- Names that must match an external schema (`whatIDid` on `ParsedStandupMarkdown`).

## Comments

- Put section semantics (`"What I did"`) in a one-line comment when the name stays short.
